00:27.823 --> 00:29.758
[Elevator dings]

00:32.494 --> 00:35.563
Morning, Jessica.

00:35.631 --> 00:37.132
Ms. Pearson.

00:37.199 --> 00:39.334
Hey, I just wanna
thank you so much

00:39.402 --> 00:42.937
for keeping me on
despite the--

00:43.005 --> 00:44.539
I guess, I just
want to let you know

00:44.607 --> 00:46.941
that I'm gonna work hard,

00:47.009 --> 00:50.712
and I'm gonna--you know,
I'm gonna make you proud.

00:50.780 --> 00:53.882
Not--not like a son--
you know--

00:53.949 --> 00:58.887
I mean, we don't really
look that much alike, I guess.

00:58.954 --> 01:00.789
That's a--that's
a strange thing to say.

01:00.856 --> 01:03.625
Uh, I just--what I meant
is that I really appreciate

01:03.693 --> 01:05.927
everything that you--
okay.

01:05.995 --> 01:09.564
[Construction sounds]

01:09.632 --> 01:11.332
- Hardman?
- One would assume.

01:11.400 --> 01:13.802
- Did he ask you?
- No, he did not.

01:15.971 --> 01:17.205
He needs your signature.

01:17.273 --> 01:20.241
And yet there was a wall
here yesterday.

01:20.309 --> 01:22.577
Well, at least he didn't ask
for his office back.

01:22.645 --> 01:23.878
I wouldn't have
given it back.

01:23.946 --> 01:25.480
I wouldn't have given
yours back to you.

01:25.548 --> 01:28.316
Unless you asked
really nicely.

01:28.384 --> 01:30.418
Isn't that--

01:30.486 --> 01:32.454
- Mine.
- Shot across the bow.

01:32.521 --> 01:34.255
No, an act of war.

01:34.323 --> 01:36.124
I love the smell of napalm
in the morning.

01:36.192 --> 01:37.926
[Sighs]

01:37.993 --> 01:40.128
It's not taupe.

01:40.196 --> 01:41.896
The color, the walls.

01:41.964 --> 01:43.465
Hardman asked for taupe.

01:43.532 --> 01:45.533
I mean, it might be tan,

01:45.601 --> 01:47.168
or beige
with a hint of mauve.

01:47.236 --> 01:48.336
But it definitely isn't taupe,

01:48.404 --> 01:49.404
and don't try to tell me
that it is.

01:49.472 --> 01:50.972
Hey, Louis,
what color shades

01:51.040 --> 01:52.240
would go well
with these taupe walls?

01:52.308 --> 01:54.175
- Enough.
- I didn't even say anything.

01:54.243 --> 01:56.044
Did you want something?

01:56.112 --> 01:57.912
Yes, chain of command
is everything to me.

01:57.980 --> 01:59.280
If I don't know
who to answer to,

01:59.348 --> 02:01.382
I might as well be living
naked on a kibbutz

02:01.450 --> 02:02.817
in the middle of Africa.

02:02.885 --> 02:04.919
An option worth considering,
though we'd miss you.

02:04.987 --> 02:05.920
[Mouths silently]
Not really.

02:05.988 --> 02:07.255
Your point?

02:07.323 --> 02:08.356
Who do I work for?

02:08.424 --> 02:09.791
I assume I work for you,

02:09.859 --> 02:11.626
but Hardman just asked me
to personally summarize

02:11.694 --> 02:12.761
every case at this firm.

02:12.828 --> 02:14.229
And I was hoping maybe
that you can

02:14.296 --> 02:15.797
let him know that
I answer to you.

02:15.865 --> 02:18.266
You do answer to me, Louis.

02:18.334 --> 02:20.201
And Daniel and I are
on the same page on this.

02:20.269 --> 02:23.872
You're the right man
for the job.

02:23.939 --> 02:27.041
Well, thank you,
that's all I needed to hear.

02:29.311 --> 02:31.012
Why'd you lie?

02:31.080 --> 02:32.180
Because you don't
let the children know

02:32.248 --> 02:35.183
that mommy and
daddy are fighting.

02:59.542 --> 03:00.742
Uh, Rachel.

03:00.810 --> 03:02.744
Hi.
I'm busy.

03:02.812 --> 03:03.778
Oh, okay.
How's it going?

03:03.846 --> 03:06.181
Busy,
so if you don't mind, I--

03:06.248 --> 03:09.551
I need to talk to you
for a second, okay?

03:09.618 --> 03:10.919
- Okay.
- Okay.

03:10.986 --> 03:13.021
So
 Zane, I need you.

03:13.088 --> 03:14.923
In my office.
Now.

03:14.990 --> 03:16.491
- You were saying?
- I just, um--

03:16.559 --> 03:18.893
What part of "now"
wasn't clear?

03:18.961 --> 03:20.495
Ugh.

03:20.563 --> 03:22.297
By the time I'm in my chair.

03:22.364 --> 03:23.298
I should probably go.

03:23.365 --> 03:26.801
No, I--

03:37.546 --> 03:40.481
I got your message.

03:50.970 --> 03:54.970
